// Data and Integration Foundations - Question Bank (GIFT)

::DI01_BigQueryDefinition::
What is BigQuery mainly used for?
{
=Storing and querying large structured datasets
~Designing browser tabs
~Replacing GitHub repositories
~Editing markdown files
}

::DI02_AgentVsDatabase::
Which statement is most accurate?
{
=The agent is not the database; it may use a tool to query the database
~The agent and the database are always the same thing
~The database writes prompts automatically
~The database replaces the cloud project
}

::DI03_ResultSetMeaning::
In data work, a result set is:
{
=The rows returned by a query
~A list of browser bookmarks
~A secret environment file
~A sub-agent prompt
}

::DI04_RAGMeaning::
What does RAG stand for?
{
=Retrieval-Augmented Generation
~Runtime Agent Gateway
~Remote Application Graph
~Rapid API Group
}

::DI05_RAGPurpose::
Why use RAG for policy questions?
{
=To ground answers in retrieved policy content
~To avoid reading documents at all
~To remove the need for tools
~To guarantee every answer is correct
}

::DI06_RAGFailureCheck::
If a policy answer seems wrong, what is a sensible first check?
{
=Whether the right documents were retrieved
~Whether the browser theme changed
~Whether GitHub has new stars
~Whether the learner closed a tab
}

